 Just renovated beautiful duplex appartment in a new building with a stunning panoramic view over Tbilisi which situated in the central of Tbilisi in Vake district on Tskhvedadze street. You can walk from the main Abashidze street or you  can come from the side of Turtle Lake with wonderful alley which leads to the building. Half distance from the building you can reach Turtle Lake and Vake Park where one can enjoy nice nature environment and fresh air.
On the first floor there are: storage and 2 bath-rooms (equipped with new branded washing machine and drier machine), kitchen (25 m2) with new electro techniques facilities, kitchen has nice balcony (12 m2) faces into the beautiful garden. The living room (60m2) has big marble fire-place (with wood storage), also the room has balcony (23m2). There are also 2 extra-rooms with independent hall, one can be used as office (20m2), another for guest bedroom (15m2). On the second floor there are a big master bed-room with private bathroom and Jacuzzi (45 m2).
Another big light room with nice view (37m2) can be transformed into 2 bedrooms. One more bathroom with steam-shower box is located on the second floor.
The most beautiful place is a big terrace (60m2) with nice flowers and bushes, big wood table and chairs you can sit and enjoy the beautiful panoramic view of Tbilisi. Small pool and finish sauna can be installed on the terrace. In the night time terrace is specially lighted that gives more charm to it. There are 2 places in garage with remote control door.

Furniture, Technique, Internet, Cable-TV, Security, Elevator, Generator, Heating system: central 
 Brand new fully furnished 1 bedroom 65sq.m. apartment with huge balcony. Located in a luxury building in Mtatsminda, just off Rustaveli avenue large and cozy   apartment with a spectacular terrace in a luxury A-class building of Besiki Business Center is the best choice. Rustaveli is main Ave of the city. All city walking routes go trough it. Besides old charming architecture, just around the corner you can find souvenir shops, best city bakery “Entree”, Chinese restaurant, wide choice of Georgian cuisine and pizza places. From our place you can walk to everything, little food markets, grocery shops, boutiques and restaurants on beloved Shardeni st, museums, theaters, movies, banks, money exchange you name it everything is just around the corner. Rustaveli Theater, Tbilisi State Conservatoire, Opera House, National Museum, Museum of Fine Arts  are just a short stroll away.
Just 30 m away from  Rustaveli ave., opposite  Marriott Tbilisi, and in the vicinity of the Parliament of Georgia, this building boasts: 24 hours reception service, free Wi-Fi,  24/7 CC TV security, central air-con system, underground parking, 4 high speed elevators, backup power/water supply, central heating and gas. First three floors of the building are hosting business center and a hotel; rest 4 floors are private apartments. 
Studio type living room and a kitchen with fridge, gas oven, microwave, electric kettle, toaster, built-in fridge and washing machine with dryer. Comfortable  sofa, convertible into a queen size bed, 43’flat screen TV, dining table with chairs, bar with couple bar chairs. Cozy bathroom with a bath; bedroom with queen size bed and orthopedic mattress, built-in wardrobe; large terrace, accessible from living room and bedroom. 
Price for long term: (3 months and up) 
1 month - $2000

Besides rest and recreation one can enjoy unforgettable views of Grigoleti nature. Grigoleti village is located close to Kolkheti national park, where visitors can enjoy bird watching as well as hunting and fishing.

 Land for sale 
The land is located at the coast of the river Natanebi on the Black Sea (Georgia) 1st zone. Total land area 112214,79 sq.m  the whole area is covered with a unique treatment (magnetic) sand, a beach and a few forests. 
The land is located near the highway Poti-Batumi, near the resort of Kobuleti (6 min. Away) and Batumi (40 min. Away), 5 km away a railway station Ureki. 
Near the land is not located and not planned improvement of industrial zones and agricultural land.
The region is famous for fishing and hunting, as well as throughout the year an extensive assortment of fruit and vegetables.
Climate is subtropical.
The area is enclosed. There is water that can be used for the operation of small craft and yachts.
The healing features of magnetic sand
Uniqueness of the area is defined    by the presence of a magnetic field of low intensity. Health features of the magnetic fields are known for a long time. They were used for the treatment by the Egyptians, the Greeks, the Indian yoga. In modern medicine, the magnetic field is widely used as a method of physical therapy called Magnetic Therapy”.  Scientific research has approved highly effectiveness of using    treatment   factors  of  magnetic sand in the following diseases: Cardiovascular diseases (hypertension stage 1-2, chronic ischemic heart disease, myocardial infarction, myocardial and others), Diseases of the musculoskeletal system (rheumatic and infectious polyarthritis in chronic stages, osteoarthritis, osteoporosis, osteochondropathy), Functional disorders of the nervous system (depression, neurosis hypertensive forms, menopausal neurosis, neuralgia and other), Childhood diseases (cerebral palsy, spinal paralysis, rickets, birth injuries, and others), Chronic urogenital disease .
Magnetic Sand of Black Sea coast has been known since the 19th century.  Scientific research has approved a beneficial effect of magnetic fields on the human body. The magnetic field exerts analgesic, anti-inflammatory effect, stimulates tissue regeneration, and the most important- improves the immune system, reduces the number of serious diseases. Magnetic therapy is widely used in gynecology, urology, in cosmetics, in sports medicine, orthopedics, cardiovascular diseases, blood, etc.   High sensitivity of the central nervous system to the action of the magnets. Magnetic fields eliminate chronic pain, accelerate blood circulation, have a vasodilator effect, affect the clotting of blood. Application for therapeutic purposes magnetic field exerts anti, antipruritic and anti-allergic effect. Magnetic fields have a positive effect on the heart, decreasing myocardial oxygen demand and increase coronary blood flow.
